---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import featherImg from "../assets/visuals/feather.png";
---

<section
    class="relative bg-featherbg py-24 px-6 flex flex-col items-center justify-center"
>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="relative flex justify-center items-center h-full">
            <Image
                src={featherImg}
                alt="Feather"
                width={500}
                height={500}
                class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-[300px] sm:max-w-[400px] md:max-w-[500px]"
                loading="eager"
            />
            <div
                class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-radial from-featherbg via-featherbg/60 to-transparent blur-2xl z-0"
            >
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div
        class="relative z-20 mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 max-w-5xl text-textDefault"
    >
        <div class="bg-surface/70 backdrop-blur-md p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg">
            <h3 class="text-highlight text-lg font-bold mb-2">What is Nexla?</h3>
            <p>
                Nexla is a platform for managing creative attentionâ€” the one thing that
                can't be automated.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-surface/70 backdrop-blur-md p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg">
            <h3 class="text-highlight text-lg font-bold mb-2">
                What does the name mean?
            </h3>
            <p>
                Nexla comes from the Aztec word for "tribute." It represents the power and
                scarcity of creative insight.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
